  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the expressive power of GNNs based on the message passing mechanism has been shown to be bounded by that of the well-known Weisfeiler-Lehman isomorphism test [98], meaning that there are inherent limits to their ability to generate different representations for structurally different input graphs.",
    "Motivated by the desire to overcome these issues, researchers have now started looking at alternative models that move away from standard message passing architectures.",
    "Efforts in this direction include, among many others, higherorder message passing architectures [106], cell complexes networks [107], networks based on diffusion processes [2,105,108].",
    "To the best of our knowledge, the application of these architectures to the 2D image understanding tasks discussed in this paper has not been explored yet.",
    "As such, we refer the readers to the referenced papers for detailed information on the respective architectures."
  ],
